    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percentage difference < 10%). Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted on the basis that quasi-static compression-bending of titanium alloy constructs is rate-insensitive and ambient temperature testing is standard practice under ASTM F1717. Overall model credibility is sufficient to support the Medium assurance level required for this Class II device submission.",
